    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1929-01-15T08:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1929-01-15T08:00:00-05:00" n="866"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d866">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">852.6363/151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Madrid</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1929-01-15T13:00:00+00:00"
                            >January 15, 1929—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 5:23 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1. Whitehouse [for] Ambassador Hammond. No agreement has yet been reached by the
                    French or American petroleum interests with Spanish Government, but Shell
                    interests have accepted settlement. Report may refer to 50 percent owned
                    Standard Oil subsidiary Sociedad Compras and Fletamentos valued at 5,000,000
                    pesetas which has been offered payment in monopoly shares selling 50 percent
                    premium. Owners have accepted offer but shares have not yet been turned
                    over.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Whitehouse</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
